local baseplate =game.Workspace.Baseplate
local function parttouched(otherPart)
	print(otherPart.Name)
end

baseplate.Touched:connect(parttouched)


--[[The function used here is known as events as it is used to trigger the function when the event is fired. 

the following partouched refers to any other part in the game that is touched by the baseplate, this happens because of the parameter otherPart. 

parttouched only acts as a reference to the parameter otherPart, whitout the parameter 'otherPart', the function parttouched is nothing.

The line baseplate.Touched:connect(parttouched) is used to connect the baseplate to the function parttouched/or the event. 

The print(otherPart.Name) is used to print the name of the part that touched the baseplate. 

You can run it yourself in roblox studios.

Thank You.
--]]

